1
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,800
Can I call you my big sister?

2
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,240
- Of course.
- Then let's go.

3
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:19,120
How do you know about all this?

4
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,440
This was between me and Kul.

5
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:22,360
Because I'm not an outsider.

6
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,280
Raka?

7
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,640
I have people who can help us.

8
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:35,640
We're back, and this time,
we're going harder

9
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,360
and bigger than ever.

10
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,280
LONG LIVE MAD DOG

11
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,440
<i>This is planting drugs.</i>

12
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,280
If nothing progresses,
the backlash is going to hit hard.

13
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:46,720
We can use social media
to manipulate public attention.

14
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,400
You people are already
good at that anyway.

15
00:03:56,280 --> 00:04:00,040
Who made our Siberian cry?

16
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:04,400
Hey, who died?

17
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:10,960
Breaking news!

18
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:15,120
It's this news, bro.
Ms. Maysa, the famous actress,

19
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,519
just announced she's getting married.

20
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:22,000
Mr. Mahasamut is marrying
Commander Singha's daughter.

21
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,480
That's so sudden.

22
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:32,560
It's more talked about than the news about
the cop who planted drugs getting killed.

23
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,760
Getting married like nothing happened,

24
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:37,480
the Minister must be pretty confident

25
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,320
that the Commander isn't involved.

26
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,280
A Minister-level guy is gonna be

27
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:46,920
dumb enough to get played
by the Commander?

28
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,480
What do you guys think? Tell us.

29
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:53,320
<i>I don't care about the dad.</i>
<i>I only care about the daughter.</i>

30
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:57,200
<i>I'm sad. I'm lonely.</i>
<i>I'm heartbroken. I love Maysa.</i>

31
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:01,240
<i>If they were really guilty,</i>
<i>they wouldn't let them get married.</i>

32
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,400
<i>Being handsome isn't a crime.</i>

33
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:04,160
<i>His daughter marrying a handsome man</i>
<i>isn't a crime.</i>

34
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,120
<i>Just get married already.</i>

35
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:09,040
<i>Political marriage</i>
<i>to distract people from the case.</i>

36
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:13,160
<i>So damn heartbroken.</i>
<i>Next life, let us be together, May.</i>

37
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:18,400
<i>Wow. Some people support them.</i>
<i>Some people are suspicious.</i>

38
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:22,560
<i>But one thing's for sure,</i>
<i>Maysa's fans are all heartbroken.</i>

39
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,320
Excuse me.

40
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:42,040
Ms. Maysa. It's time.

41
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,880
I'd like to talk to Ms. Maysa
for a moment.

42
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:57,160
And Ms. Fahsai didn't come with you?

43
00:05:58,040 --> 00:06:00,200
Yong, leave us for a moment.

44
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,520
Yes.

45
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,240
Aren't you afraid Yong will tell Fahsai?

46
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:15,920
I'm afraid…

47
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,600
of not seeing you more.

48
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,960
I had to come see you

49
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,800
before you changed
your surname to Samut's.

50
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:39,480
I never thought
today would come either.

51
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:44,440
He's very smart for choosing you.

52
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,920
If he were even a little dumber,

53
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:53,480
maybe it wouldn't hurt so much
seeing you beside him.

54
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,760
Why be afraid

55
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,680
when my heart belongs to you?

56
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:09,880
We still have so much time together.

57
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:24,800
I'll wait for the day
we can be together openly.

58
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:28,280
No matter how long it takes, I'll wait.

59
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:32,000
You're making my heart race.

60
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:36,640
Just like first love, right?

61
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,280
That's how I feel too.

62
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,640
First love.

63
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:34,240
Ms. Fahsai, are you done yet?

64
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:37,600
- Let's go.
- Why are we rushing?

65
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:41,320
I don't want to greet Dad's guests.

66
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:44,720
They only talk about politics
and benefits.

67
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:48,760
Oh, not the ballroom.

68
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,240
Go to Ms. Maysa's room.

69
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,920
Mr. Wayu and Ms. Maysa

70
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,240
are in her room talking alone right now.

71
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,680
I couldn't stay and be nosy--

72
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:01,200
I mean, stay and keep watch.

73
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:05,200
Let's go. We need to know
what they're talking about.

74
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:07,400
Leaving them alone like that
is inappropriate.

75
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,360
Let's go.

76
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,120
Maybe they have personal matters
to discuss.

77
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,760
Otherwise, why would
they do something inappropriate?

78
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,520
Huh?

79
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,200
Come on.

80
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:20,640
Hurry up.

81
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:27,960
Don't let him get away with it.
Make a huge scene.

82
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:30,720
Pressure him until he tells the truth.

83
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:43,120
I stopped by to greet Ms. Maysa.

84
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,360
Come on. Let's go inside.

85
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,200
Just like that?

86
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,880
- Yes?
- We've reached the target house.

87
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,400
Okay.

88
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,160
Done.

89
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,160
Okay.

90
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,200
Food delivery.

91
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,120
Let's go.

92
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,080
I didn't order this. It's not mine.

93
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:14,040
Ms. Maysa asked me to bring it.

94
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:17,760
I'm a staff member from the hotel hosting
Ms. Maysa and Mr. Mahasamut's wedding.

95
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:20,720
Ms. May is always so kind.

96
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,800
Alright.

97
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:26,600
- Thanks.
- Yes. I'll get going then.

98
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:46,040
This door is the best way
to avoid the maid's room.

99
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:47,440
Do it.

100
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,960
Let's go.

101
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,160
This is the study.

102
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:12,280
The love I have for her,

103
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:16,520
from the very first day

104
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,720
until today,

105
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,560
everything is still the same.

106
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:41,440
I love her the same way I always have.

107
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:49,520
And I always will.

108
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:02,720
I never thought Mr. Mahasamut
could be this sweet.

109
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:07,240
Now, let's hear how the bride feels.

110
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,680
I want you to know

111
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:21,840
that you are
the most special person to me.

112
00:14:28,280 --> 00:14:30,120
You're the only one I love.

113
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:45,960
And that was the bride and groom sharing
their heartfelt feelings for each other.

114
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:48,720
Next, I'd like to invite the couple

115
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:53,160
to greet our honored guests here today.

116
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,440
- Yes.
- Please.

117
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:55,400
Let's go.

118
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:09,120
Is something wrong, Dad?

119
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,960
OFFLINE

120
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,560
Why can't I access the CCTV at home?

121
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:23,080
Good thing you've been here often.

122
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:25,880
If we'd had to find this room ourselves,
it would've taken forever.

123
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,280
Split up and search.

124
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,760
Why isn't the house phone working?

125
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,320
Mek isn't answering either.

126
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,400
Did you unlock it yet?

127
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,160
Not yet.

128
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,680
He must've stored the file
on the computer.

129
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:30,520
But what could help us guess the password?

130
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,600
Or maybe…

131
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,920
these?

132
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,200
- I'll be back.
- Okay.

133
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:07,400
Hey. Excuse me for a moment.

134
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:08,960
Okay.

135
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:14,560
Hello.

136
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:17,280
Is something wrong?

137
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:22,319
I had some unfinished business
to discuss with your father,

138
00:17:22,839 --> 00:17:23,960
but I can't find him.

139
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,240
Dad went home.

140
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:30,080
He said the CCTV at home
was having problems.

141
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:50,920
Yes?

142
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:54,760
Singha has gone back. Be careful.

143
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:56,480
Got it.

144
00:17:57,640 --> 00:18:00,000
Wayu said Singha has left the venue.

145
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:06,880
Drive the car somewhere else.
Singha has left the wedding.

146
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:08,720
Okay, okay, okay.

147
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:22,920
He's very proud of these plaques.

148
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,440
The password must be hidden somewhere.

149
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:37,760
He's at the front gate.

150
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:40,680
Singha's at the front gate already.

151
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,520
Plan B. Let's go.

152
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,600
Mek.

153
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,480
Mek.

154
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,120
You dare sleep on duty?

155
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:17,360
Why the hell is the house so dark?

156
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,480
Maybe something short-circuited, sir.

157
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:23,680
It was working earlier.

158
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,960
I'll go check right now, sir.

159
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:26,880
Go.

160
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,800
- Did you unlock it yet?
- Not yet.

161
00:19:57,400 --> 00:20:00,320
Look, there are numbers here.

162
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,400
Try September 30, 2021.

163
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:05,160
30092564.

164
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:47,680
There's nothing that tells us anything.

165
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:54,720
<i>Soyez le soleil.</i>

166
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,600
Be the sun.

167
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:59,760
I think I know this phrase.

168
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,920
It really can turn into numbers.

169
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:12,560
- Try it.
- Seven, one, three, seven, zero…

170
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:19,360
Two, three.

171
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:22,800
Y, zero, five?

172
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,280
- Y?
- Y?

173
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:27,240
Y.

174
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:28,480
Or maybe it's zero?

175
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:30,600
It can't be that easy.

176
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:38,360
Or it's the english word "why?"

177
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,200
"Why"

178
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:44,000
- Why?
- But what number would that be?

179
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:45,080
Three.

180
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:49,840
Three-zero-five.

181
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:55,320
- Yes.
- Got it.

182
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:58,600
Then I'll start downloading
the data first.

183
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:42,000
SENDING MESSAGE TO SAM (SMS/MMS)

184
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:57,000
Excuse me.

185
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:06,680
The architect for The Reward asked for
an emergency meeting about the clubhouse.

186
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,680
I have to go.

187
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,040
Good then.

188
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,880
You can go home with me tonight.

189
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:20,400
But this is your brother's wedding.

190
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,920
You have to stay until the end.

191
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:25,640
You can go.

192
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:29,280
I'll keep Fahsai company
and take her back to our house.

193
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:33,560
See you at home then.

194
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:37,240
Excuse me.

195
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,200
Let's go take pictures at the backdrop.

196
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:53,480
- Okay.
- Let's go.

197
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:02,720
I had to download everything.
There wasn't time to check.

198
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:05,720
It's okay. Just making it back alive
was already lucky.

199
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:07,400
We'll go through it slowly.

200
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:12,280
Here.

201
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:13,920
Heaven Club.

202
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:20,000
MINISTER RAKCHART

203
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:24,000
Almost getting shot to death
wasn't for nothing.

204
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:31,440
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

205
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:35,400
Oh, damn it.

206
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:37,840
Why is this footage
from the old man's party?

207
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:42,760
There is still a lot more. Keep looking.

208
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:44,160
It has to be in here somewhere.

209
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:47,120
Commander Singha wouldn't make
the file name obvious for us to guess.

210
00:24:48,240 --> 00:24:49,560
We have to go through them one by one.

211
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:08,080
You're going out?

212
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,800
But this is our wedding night.

213
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:16,800
So?

214
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:19,520
You wanted me to marry you,
didn't you? I already did.

215
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:24,520
If anyone sees you outside,
they'll gossip nonstop.

216
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:26,920
Why don't you ever think
about my reputation?

217
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:29,360
You'll look bad too.

218
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:32,360
The groom going out partying
on his wedding night like this?

219
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:33,720
Then go tell the media

220
00:25:34,760 --> 00:25:38,600
I'm out working for the people.

221
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:42,000
Isn't that what you always say anyway?

222
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:50,200
You're already good at acting.

223
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:53,160
What are you afraid of?

224
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:19,400
Boss.

225
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:23,400
About Dr. Sakda, the one
you told me to negotiate with,

226
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:25,000
I handled it already.

227
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:27,160
So how much did he want?

228
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:28,400
He wouldn't take money, sir.

229
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:30,760
He even kicked me out.

230
00:26:30,840 --> 00:26:33,280
What the hell? Huh?

231
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:37,000
What kind of cursed day is this?

232
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:40,600
I had to sit through that stupid ceremony,
and now I have to deal with this bullshit.

233
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:48,120
Go, go. Just get out of here.

234
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:13,240
What's wrong?

235
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:15,520
Did you have a fight with the bride?

236
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:18,480
No.

237
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:26,160
You've been in this industry a long time.

238
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:30,640
Do you know anyone
who can talk to Dr. Sakda Julpratheep?

239
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,800
Dr. Sakda?

240
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:37,200
The chairman
of the railway bidding project?

241
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:39,080
Yes.

242
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:44,040
You know him? How well?

243
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:45,920
I really need this project.

244
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:48,400
Can you help me?

245
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:52,640
I don't know him personally.

246
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:54,680
Whoa.

247
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:56,560
Then why didn't you say that
from the start?

248
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:58,920
You let me keep talking for nothing.

249
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,680
Don't get upset yet.

250
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:04,840
Even though I don't know him,

251
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:08,600
I do know who we can send to talk to him.

252
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:15,480
Well.

253
00:28:16,640 --> 00:28:19,120
Is Ms. May doing okay, Ms. Yiwa?

254
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:22,960
I really don't know.

255
00:28:23,040 --> 00:28:26,040
We're not working together anymore.

256
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:27,080
You didn't know?

257
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:34,360
Really? I didn't know. I'm so sorry.

258
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:37,560
I almost spilled the tea.

259
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:45,360
So what were you going to gossip about?

260
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:49,600
Well…

261
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:53,960
I heard that Dr. Sakda,

262
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:57,960
the chairman of the billion-baht
railway bidding committee,

263
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:02,760
really likes Ms. May.
He's liked her for a long time.

264
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:05,480
The high-society crowd

265
00:29:05,560 --> 00:29:08,840
have been gossiping that he desperately
wants to meet her in person.

266
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:15,440
I was even secretly thinking someone
must've arranged for Ms. May to meet him.

267
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:20,360
May really is incredibly charming.

268
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:24,760
She's beautiful and talented.
I'm a fan myself.

269
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:25,680
Right?

270
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:29,280
I don't think May would go though.

271
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:31,040
She already has Mr. Samut.

272
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:37,320
It's just drinking and listening
to music together, that's all.

273
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:40,120
And I secretly heard

274
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:42,760
that if you just go have dinner with him,

275
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:46,840
you get paid hundreds of thousands.
If it were me, I'd go for 12,000.

276
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:49,080
Money's hard to earn these days. Right?

277
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,680
Exactly, exactly.

278
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:54,800
How's this hairstyle?

279
00:29:54,880 --> 00:29:55,800
It's good.

280
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,120
Don't let him get away with it.

281
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:21,040
Make a huge scene.
Pressure him until he tells the truth.

282
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:21,960
Come on.

283
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:34,160
I stopped by to greet Ms. Maysa.

284
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:42,680
Are you a person or an owl?

285
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:45,480
Why are you still awake?

286
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,160
Are you waiting for me?

287
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,440
Sorry. The meeting just ended.

288
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,160
Come on. Let's go to bed.

289
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:04,800
I'm not sleepy yet.

290
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:07,760
You should go shower first.

291
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:15,760
But when I come out, I have to see you,

292
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:17,480
okay?

293
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:23,720
Is something wrong?

294
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:31,040
Then is there anything
you want to tell me?

295
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:36,040
The floor plan still isn't finalized yet.

296
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:37,480
There are a lot of parts that need fixing.

297
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:43,000
I haven't told you because
I didn't want you to stress over it.

298
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:47,320
Come on, let's go sleep
before you get sick.

299
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:49,120
I want to sit here a little longer.

300
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:55,200
Okay.

301
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,600
But don't stay up too late.

302
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:02,000
Sleeping alone feels lonely.

303
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:31,920
Isn't it funny?

304
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:35,880
On our wedding night,
the groom goes out partying

305
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:38,440
and doesn't care
about the bride's feelings at all.

306
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:41,160
He shouldn't treat you like this.

307
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,520
I never should've chosen him.

308
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:52,960
If the first night is already like this,
then what about all the nights after this?

309
00:33:54,560 --> 00:33:56,400
How much longer do I have to endure this?

310
00:33:58,440 --> 00:34:00,480
I never should've let him have you.

311
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:06,200
Then hold me tight.

312
00:34:08,159 --> 00:34:09,760
So I won't go back to him again.

313
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,080
Fahsai knows I came out.

314
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:22,280
I have to go back first.

315
00:36:31,560 --> 00:36:32,960
We have to be patient.

316
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:38,320
As long as we haven't gained every benefit
we can from Samut and Fahsai yet,

317
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:42,240
we can't let them know

318
00:36:43,080 --> 00:36:44,640
that we're secretly together.

319
00:36:48,880 --> 00:36:51,840
I'll have my driver take you home.

320
00:36:54,680 --> 00:36:58,640
And you don't need to care
about Samut abandoning you tonight.

321
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,360
You're worth far more than that.

322
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:34,480
<i>I'm out now. Thanks for helping me.</i>

323
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:45,440
No big deal, bro. I stay up late anyway.

324
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:17,640
Where are you going?

325
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:20,720
I have an event today.
I'll have to face reporters.

326
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,680
And if you're not there
and they ask about you,

327
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:23,920
what am I supposed to say?

328
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:26,080
Then don't go.

329
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:31,600
What's wrong with you?
I already accepted the job.

330
00:38:31,680 --> 00:38:34,800
I already called the organizer
and told them to find someone else.

331
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:39,200
The more you act like this, the more
suspicious the reporters will get.

332
00:38:39,880 --> 00:38:41,440
And if they call me and ask questions,

333
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:42,840
what am I supposed to tell them?

334
00:38:45,800 --> 00:38:48,320
Just tell them you can't go

335
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:52,360
because you're going
on your honeymoon with Mr. Samut.

336
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:13,400
I never thought you'd actually make time
to bring me here for our honeymoon.

337
00:39:14,160 --> 00:39:15,800
I know you like the beach.

338
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:19,400
But one night here is okay, right?

339
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:23,240
Even this already makes me happy.

340
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:28,440
It's been such a long time since the two
of us got to travel alone together.

341
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:38,760
I'll make more time
and bring you here more often.

342
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:42,880
You're so kind.

343
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:45,640
Well, we're married now.

344
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:48,880
I want to try being
a good husband to you too.

345
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:54,120
Maysa,

346
00:39:55,520 --> 00:39:57,520
if we take business

347
00:39:58,120 --> 00:39:59,920
and social status out of it,

348
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:03,760
have you ever really loved me?

349
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:16,040
Why would you ask me that?

350
00:40:16,920 --> 00:40:20,320
You know how much I love you.

351
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:22,800
Even though…

352
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:26,760
you've made me cry so many times…

353
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:34,320
- I endured it.
- Can you do me a favor?

354
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:37,400
Can you forget about all of that?

355
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:40,400
Let's start over from zero.

356
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:44,760
Can we live happily together like this?

357
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,240
Can you do it?

358
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:56,280
I never thought that what Dad told me,
that I should endure,

359
00:40:57,160 --> 00:40:58,600
would lead to a day like this.

360
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:01,680
Thank you so much.

361
00:41:03,080 --> 00:41:05,040
I'm really happy.

362
00:41:06,160 --> 00:41:07,320
I love you.

363
00:41:25,960 --> 00:41:28,280
I searched all the way to the last file
and couldn't find it.

364
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:31,520
So what now?

365
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:34,920
Do you think Maysa knows anything?

366
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:39,000
I don't want to make a move
and ask her yet.

367
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:43,120
We still have
the Dr. Sakda job waiting for us.

368
00:41:45,280 --> 00:41:48,800
So where the hell did he hide the clip?

369
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:54,800
- Or he already destroyed all the evidence?
- No way.

370
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:59,320
This is the only thing
that can save his life.

371
00:41:59,400 --> 00:42:01,480
And I believe there are multiple copies.

372
00:42:01,560 --> 00:42:04,200
We just don't know where they are.

373
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:14,280
What are you yelling for? You scared me.

374
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:16,800
If we can't find the evidence clip,

375
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:19,320
then we find other evidence instead.

376
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:20,800
They have a lot of enemies.

377
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:24,320
We just need to make
the evidence come to us.

378
00:42:36,840 --> 00:42:40,280
HERE THEY ARE

379
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:42,160
I'VE BEEN WAITING

380
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:46,440
IS THIS THE NEXT PART
OF THE ONE FROM THE LAST LIVE?

381
00:42:46,520 --> 00:42:49,000
LET'S CONTINUE WATCHING IT

382
00:43:01,520 --> 00:43:03,160
That's the end of the clip, everyone.

383
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:06,400
Last time, thieves disguised as police
barged into the livestream,

384
00:43:06,480 --> 00:43:08,080
so we didn't get to finish showing it.

385
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:12,640
Just imagine what would've happened
to the beautiful girl in that clip

386
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:17,040
if those wonderful police officers
hadn't stormed into the club for a search.

387
00:43:17,120 --> 00:43:20,080
Hey, you accidentally
let the word "club" slip out.

388
00:43:20,840 --> 00:43:25,200
I wonder what club it was?

389
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:26,880
<i>What club? Anyone know?</i>

390
00:43:26,960 --> 00:43:28,640
<i>Is it HV Club? I wanna know.</i>

391
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:31,720
<i>The place looks luxurious as hell,</i>

392
00:43:31,800 --> 00:43:34,280
<i>but they drug women there. Trash.</i>

393
00:43:34,360 --> 00:43:37,640
<i>She could barely walk straight.</i>
<i>She was definitely drugged.</i>

394
00:43:37,720 --> 00:43:40,560
<i>A club at that level</i>
<i>would never get raided easily.</i>

395
00:43:40,640 --> 00:43:42,120
<i>A minister is backing it.</i>

396
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:46,400
<i>It's not Hell, but Hea… What was it again?</i>

397
00:43:46,480 --> 00:43:47,920
Heaven Club.

398
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:50,760
Mad Dog knows. Everyone knows.

399
00:43:50,840 --> 00:43:52,400
But we can't say it publicly

400
00:43:52,480 --> 00:43:54,400
or we'll get sued, everyone.

401
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:57,280
This livestream isn't just for fun.

402
00:43:57,360 --> 00:43:58,800
Anyone who's been victimized,

403
00:43:58,880 --> 00:44:02,080
anyone bullied,

404
00:44:02,160 --> 00:44:04,960
threatened, exploited, assaulted,

405
00:44:05,040 --> 00:44:07,440
or forced into doing things
they didn't want to do at that club…

406
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:11,160
You can contact us through the livestream

407
00:44:11,240 --> 00:44:13,360
or our inbox.

408
00:44:15,520 --> 00:44:16,600
Remember this.

409
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:19,440
There's nothing shameful about it.

410
00:44:19,960 --> 00:44:23,760
We're victims.
We're the ones who were wronged.

411
00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:27,640
<i>The people who did those disgusting things</i>
<i>are the ones who should be ashamed.</i>

412
00:44:40,000 --> 00:44:43,040
Yong, do you know Heaven Club?
Have you ever been there?

413
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:47,800
You've never been there before,
Ms. Fahsai?

414
00:44:49,040 --> 00:44:51,680
I never wanted to go,
so I never asked anyone about it.

415
00:44:54,520 --> 00:44:57,360
Your father and Mr. Samut probably
thought it wasn't suitable for you.

416
00:44:57,440 --> 00:44:58,480
That's why they never took you there.

417
00:45:07,320 --> 00:45:08,520
Not suitable how?

418
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:13,360
Well…

419
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:18,480
It's the kind of place
men go to have fun.

420
00:45:19,200 --> 00:45:22,480
Drinking, partying,

421
00:45:22,560 --> 00:45:24,120
and there are girls sitting around
drinking with them too.

422
00:45:24,200 --> 00:45:25,480
Like that.

423
00:45:26,440 --> 00:45:27,280
That's all?

424
00:45:28,360 --> 00:45:32,280
And once everyone gets drunk
and enjoys themselves,

425
00:45:32,360 --> 00:45:34,560
if they like each other enough,
then maybe…

426
00:45:41,400 --> 00:45:42,480
They sleep together.

427
00:45:43,640 --> 00:45:44,600
Oh my.

428
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:46,000
Yes.

429
00:45:47,400 --> 00:45:49,560
If you understood that fast,
you should've said so,

430
00:45:49,640 --> 00:45:51,040
then I wouldn't have had to…

431
00:45:51,920 --> 00:45:53,000
Yeah.

432
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:55,520
Those drinking girls,

433
00:45:55,600 --> 00:45:57,560
do they willingly go with those men?

434
00:46:04,440 --> 00:46:08,640
If both sides consented,
then it shouldn't become news, right?

435
00:46:10,840 --> 00:46:13,440
I'd rather not comment on that.

436
00:46:27,080 --> 00:46:28,080
This is unbelievable.

437
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:31,280
I never thought there'd come a day
when you'd be the one

438
00:46:31,360 --> 00:46:33,680
summoning the commander for questioning.

439
00:46:37,360 --> 00:46:39,120
Hello.

440
00:46:39,200 --> 00:46:40,120
Hello, ma'am.

441
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:41,520
I bought this for you.

442
00:46:42,360 --> 00:46:43,560
All of this?

443
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:44,760
Please share it.

444
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:46,480
Thank you.

445
00:46:47,040 --> 00:46:49,400
Getting to eat delicious food
before heading into battle?

446
00:46:49,480 --> 00:46:51,160
This is amazing. Thank you so much.

447
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:53,360
Here.

448
00:46:53,440 --> 00:46:54,480
This one's yours.

449
00:46:58,640 --> 00:47:01,840
In case Commander Singha
gets angry and shoots you or something,

450
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:03,680
at least you'll get
one delicious final meal.

451
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:04,880
Wow…

452
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:07,680
A delicious final meal?

453
00:47:07,760 --> 00:47:09,520
Captain's not gonna die that easily.

454
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:13,160
He's gonna stick around long enough
for you to keep bringing him food.

455
00:47:13,240 --> 00:47:14,320
Right, Captain?

456
00:47:16,640 --> 00:47:17,680
And from now on,

457
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:20,680
you won't have to keep going out to eat
with Kaitod alone.

458
00:47:20,760 --> 00:47:21,720
Right?

459
00:47:21,800 --> 00:47:24,320
Sergeant, do you still want to eat
in peace?

460
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:30,680
Then I'll excuse myself and go enjoy
this food with the guys first. Thank you.

461
00:47:30,760 --> 00:47:32,000
You're welcome.

462
00:47:34,680 --> 00:47:36,120
Hurry up and eat.

463
00:48:15,120 --> 00:48:16,520
You're worried about the commander?

464
00:48:21,880 --> 00:48:23,000
Well…

465
00:48:25,160 --> 00:48:26,400
Not really.

466
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:30,080
If someone breaks the law,
I have to deal with it.

467
00:48:36,800 --> 00:48:38,440
I just keep thinking…

468
00:48:39,640 --> 00:48:41,480
can power and money

469
00:48:42,880 --> 00:48:45,720
really change someone that completely?

470
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:50,720
Back when Commander Singha
was just a lieutenant, he was a good cop.

471
00:48:58,760 --> 00:49:00,720
You need to be very careful.

472
00:49:02,560 --> 00:49:06,240
Because that lieutenant
died a long time ago.

473
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:11,560
All that's left now is the Commander
you have to deal with.

474
00:49:23,360 --> 00:49:24,440
Are you worried about me?

475
00:49:26,600 --> 00:49:27,440
Yes.

476
00:49:29,280 --> 00:49:30,920
I'm worried about you.

477
00:49:32,640 --> 00:49:34,200
Very worried.

478
00:49:58,200 --> 00:49:59,240
What's so urgent

479
00:50:00,160 --> 00:50:01,600
that you had to come to my house?

480
00:50:02,720 --> 00:50:03,560
It's a day off today.

481
00:50:04,720 --> 00:50:05,920
Aren't you resting?

482
00:50:07,560 --> 00:50:10,880
We can't rest. This morning,
Sergeant Pichai Piannuam,

483
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:14,080
one of the officers
from your team who disappeared,

484
00:50:14,680 --> 00:50:18,000
turned himself in and confessed

485
00:50:18,800 --> 00:50:20,400
to planting drugs at Kon La Yum.

486
00:50:21,800 --> 00:50:25,120
And he also implicated you
as the one who gave the order.

487
00:50:25,200 --> 00:50:26,440
That's not true.

488
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:29,960
He's angry at me

489
00:50:30,800 --> 00:50:32,760
because I put him
on disciplinary probation

490
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:36,440
for drinking on duty.

491
00:50:36,960 --> 00:50:38,400
That's why he's framing me.

492
00:50:39,720 --> 00:50:41,200
Where is he right now?

493
00:50:54,960 --> 00:50:58,000
<i>The suspect is now officially</i>
<i>under police protection.</i>

494
00:50:58,080 --> 00:50:59,880
I'd like to invite you

495
00:51:00,400 --> 00:51:02,240
to give a statement
at police headquarters.

496
00:51:02,320 --> 00:51:03,680
Give a statement?

497
00:51:04,760 --> 00:51:07,520
Without any actual evidence against me?

498
00:51:07,600 --> 00:51:09,720
You have the right to call a lawyer.

499
00:51:10,640 --> 00:51:12,800
And you can also defend yourself

500
00:51:13,880 --> 00:51:14,840
regarding the drug-planting case…

501
00:51:16,480 --> 00:51:18,880
as well as ordering
Sergeant Pichai to silence me.

502
00:51:22,240 --> 00:51:24,560
Commander, if you're truly innocent,

503
00:51:24,640 --> 00:51:26,760
nobody can make you a suspect.

504
00:51:30,360 --> 00:51:33,240
I'll report directly
to my superior myself.

505
00:51:34,720 --> 00:51:35,560
I'll wait right here.

506
00:51:41,720 --> 00:51:44,960
If you're going to change into uniform,
I don't think that'll be necessary.

507
00:51:45,800 --> 00:51:48,160
An order has already come down
from the Police Commissioner,

508
00:51:48,920 --> 00:51:51,960
placing you on temporary suspension

509
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:55,400
for the sake of fairness
to all parties involved.

510
00:51:56,160 --> 00:51:57,320
So…

511
00:51:58,760 --> 00:51:59,600
Please.

512
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:06,920
Then just send someone to silence him.

513
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:08,800
How the hell am I supposed to do that?

514
00:52:09,480 --> 00:52:11,440
Right now, he's under witness protection.

515
00:52:12,280 --> 00:52:14,880
I just finished giving my statement
to the Deputy Commissioner.

516
00:52:14,960 --> 00:52:16,720
And I've already been suspended too.

517
00:52:18,000 --> 00:52:19,000
So,

518
00:52:19,920 --> 00:52:22,280
can you speak
to the Police Commissioner for me?

519
00:52:24,200 --> 00:52:26,560
The election's close now.

520
00:52:27,760 --> 00:52:30,120
I can't just casually move around
meeting important people.

521
00:52:30,200 --> 00:52:32,600
The reporters are watching me,

522
00:52:33,280 --> 00:52:35,480
and the opposition party is too.

523
00:52:36,000 --> 00:52:37,480
I can't afford to make reckless moves.

524
00:52:38,240 --> 00:52:39,960
So you're not going to help me?

525
00:52:40,960 --> 00:52:43,720
Right now, I've got
an important bid project to secure.

526
00:52:43,800 --> 00:52:46,320
If helping someone risks getting me
dragged by society

527
00:52:46,400 --> 00:52:48,800
and social media,
then I'm not taking that risk.

528
00:52:50,960 --> 00:52:54,560
Once the bidding's over,
we'll talk again.

529
00:52:54,640 --> 00:52:56,480
By then, will it even be in time?

530
00:52:58,080 --> 00:53:03,800
Investigations and procedures
take time, don't they?

531
00:53:04,600 --> 00:53:08,800
You just have to lose a little face
and reputation. What's the big deal?

532
00:53:09,840 --> 00:53:10,960
Hm?

533
00:53:11,920 --> 00:53:14,560
And don't contact me again.

534
00:53:14,640 --> 00:53:18,080
Reporters are already suspicious.
I don't want to get dragged down with you.

535
00:53:18,680 --> 00:53:21,200
So now you're just going to throw me away?

536
00:53:22,360 --> 00:53:24,800
I did everything for you.

537
00:53:25,320 --> 00:53:26,920
Didn't you ever think
we were on the same side?

538
00:53:27,520 --> 00:53:29,560
At the very least,
my daughter is your wife.

539
00:53:29,640 --> 00:53:32,320
I am trying to help you already.

540
00:53:32,400 --> 00:53:33,400
You're not satisfied?

541
00:53:34,440 --> 00:53:36,480
If you don't want to wait, then don't.

542
00:53:37,200 --> 00:53:38,680
Go find someone else to help you.

543
00:53:39,840 --> 00:53:40,760
Wait, Mr. Samut.

544
00:53:43,280 --> 00:53:45,600
Samut! You fucking bastard!

545
00:53:46,440 --> 00:53:48,200
How the hell can you do this to me?

546
00:54:01,280 --> 00:54:03,040
- Please consider it.
- Hello, hello.

547
00:54:03,120 --> 00:54:04,920
Hello.

548
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:06,400
- Did you just arrive?
- Mr. Sakda.

549
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:09,640
- Hello.
- Hello.

550
00:54:10,480 --> 00:54:11,840
- Excuse me.
- Please.

551
00:54:13,880 --> 00:54:15,400
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

552
00:54:16,520 --> 00:54:17,560
This is Maysa.

553
00:54:19,120 --> 00:54:19,960
Hello, sir.

554
00:54:21,600 --> 00:54:24,960
Mr. Samut praises you to me all the time.

555
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:26,680
I'm finally meeting you in person.

556
00:54:27,200 --> 00:54:29,640
You're even more distinguished
and charismatic in real life.

557
00:54:30,600 --> 00:54:33,600
Mr. Samut talks about you quite often too.

558
00:54:33,680 --> 00:54:37,680
Honestly, you're far more beautiful
and charming in person than on screen.

559
00:54:38,560 --> 00:54:39,480
Thank you.

560
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:41,600
Do you have time to watch dramas too?

561
00:54:42,960 --> 00:54:44,480
Even if I didn't, I'd make time.

562
00:54:45,080 --> 00:54:46,440
I'm your fan.

563
00:54:48,040 --> 00:54:51,360
Thank you so much
for supporting my work, sir.

564
00:54:53,080 --> 00:54:55,560
Mr. Sakda is the chairman
of an electric railway bidding committee.

565
00:54:55,640 --> 00:54:57,880
It's worth multi-billion baht.

566
00:54:59,280 --> 00:55:02,840
You have a super-premium-level fan
right here, May.

567
00:55:05,400 --> 00:55:09,080
Then may this fan have the honor
of taking a photo with you?

568
00:55:13,600 --> 00:55:14,800
Of course.

569
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:56,800
Hello, Ms. Fahsai.

570
00:55:56,880 --> 00:55:57,760
Hello.

571
00:55:57,840 --> 00:55:59,800
Are you meeting Mr. Samut tonight?

572
00:56:01,320 --> 00:56:04,200
Samut will be here soon.
He's stuck at a ministry reception.

573
00:56:04,280 --> 00:56:06,480
So he asked me to take care of the guests.

574
00:56:07,080 --> 00:56:10,600
He asked you to personally
take care of the guests?

575
00:56:11,720 --> 00:56:13,440
Yes. Is something wrong?

576
00:56:14,040 --> 00:56:17,920
Oh, no, not at all. Excuse me.

577
00:56:42,120 --> 00:56:43,640
Stay here tonight.

578
00:56:46,080 --> 00:56:47,960
Why aren't we going home?

579
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:50,720
Or do you want a change of atmosphere?

580
00:56:54,720 --> 00:56:55,600
Do you like it?

581
00:57:01,320 --> 00:57:03,600
I'll go get you something warm to drink.

582
00:57:25,920 --> 00:57:27,400
Why is it suddenly so hot?

583
00:57:46,280 --> 00:57:47,520
Please take care of her for me.

584
00:57:47,600 --> 00:57:49,080
Don't worry.

585
00:57:49,680 --> 00:57:51,560
And what about our deal?

586
00:57:52,280 --> 00:57:55,360
Well, if May is in the room,
then the deal stands.

587
00:58:48,760 --> 00:58:49,600
May.

588
00:58:56,800 --> 00:59:00,040
Sir? How did you get in here?

589
00:59:01,240 --> 00:59:04,680
Mr. Samut! Mr. Samut!

590
00:59:28,560 --> 00:59:29,720
Mr. Samut!

591
00:59:30,240 --> 00:59:31,920
Stop wasting your breath screaming.

592
00:59:32,000 --> 00:59:34,600
Samut was the one who let me in.

593
00:59:36,960 --> 00:59:38,520
Let me go. Let me go.

594
00:59:38,600 --> 00:59:41,160
You should just stay still and behave.

595
00:59:41,240 --> 00:59:43,400
No, I won't.

596
00:59:43,480 --> 00:59:46,520
I won't. Let me go.
How can you do this to me?

597
00:59:46,600 --> 00:59:50,040
Mr. Samut, how could you
let him do this to me?

598
00:59:50,120 --> 00:59:51,800
You'll have to ask Samut that yourself.

599
00:59:52,800 --> 00:59:54,480
He's the one who offered you to me.

600
00:59:57,240 --> 00:59:59,360
No! No!

601
00:59:59,440 --> 01:00:01,160
I won't sleep with you!

602
01:00:01,240 --> 01:00:04,560
Let me go!

603
01:00:04,640 --> 01:00:06,120
Let go!

604
01:00:10,200 --> 01:00:13,920
Let go of me.

605
01:00:14,000 --> 01:00:15,960
Where are you taking me?

606
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:18,720
I want to go home.

607
01:00:19,360 --> 01:00:20,760
Let go.

608
01:00:35,720 --> 01:00:37,800
- Let's have some fun together.
- No!

609
01:00:38,720 --> 01:00:39,800
‪Please stop!

610
01:00:39,880 --> 01:00:41,240
Okay?

611
01:00:45,600 --> 01:00:48,040
- She's beautiful.
- Let go!

612
01:00:49,880 --> 01:00:51,920
- She's beautiful.
- You can't do this!

613
01:00:52,000 --> 01:00:53,160
You can take her.

614
01:00:53,240 --> 01:00:54,920
- Go open a room.
- Let go!

615
01:00:55,000 --> 01:00:56,400
No! You can't do this!

616
01:00:56,480 --> 01:00:58,000
This girl's really beautiful.

617
01:00:58,080 --> 01:01:00,120
Someone, help!

618
01:01:00,200 --> 01:01:01,640
‪Stop! Let go!

619
01:01:12,520 --> 01:01:14,200
<i>And you dared to do this to my daughter?</i>

620
01:01:14,800 --> 01:01:16,160
<i>You sent my daughter</i>
<i>to sleep with another man,</i>

621
01:01:16,240 --> 01:01:17,400
<i>even though she's your wife!</i>

622
01:01:18,560 --> 01:01:20,680
You're out of bullets,
aren't you, Commander?

623
01:01:20,760 --> 01:01:21,640
Black Doc!

624
01:01:24,640 --> 01:01:25,640
Wayu!

625
01:01:27,120 --> 01:01:28,400
Stop lying already!

626
01:01:29,240 --> 01:01:30,160
- Stop it!
- Fahsai.

627
01:01:30,240 --> 01:01:33,640
<i>I can't stand being near you,</i>
<i>even for another second.</i>

628
01:01:33,720 --> 01:01:35,480
Before becoming Prime Minister,

629
01:01:35,560 --> 01:01:36,920
become a decent human being first.

630
01:01:37,000 --> 01:01:38,240
- Yes.
- Right.

631
01:01:38,320 --> 01:01:39,440
- Yes.
- How can you do this?

632
01:01:39,520 --> 01:01:41,080
I'm not answering any questions.

633
01:01:41,160 --> 01:01:43,040
- Please, everyone.
- Please wait.

634
01:01:43,120 --> 01:01:44,560
This is the police!

635
01:01:45,320 --> 01:01:48,040
<i>Mr. Mahasamut Pasukampanart,</i>

636
01:01:48,120 --> 01:01:49,760
<i>come down and give your statement</i>
<i>to the authorities.</i>

637
01:01:50,440 --> 01:01:51,360
Run them over.

638
01:01:52,840 --> 01:01:53,720
- Hey!
- Stop!

639
01:01:54,320 --> 01:01:57,080
I wanted to come say goodbye to you.

640
01:01:57,160 --> 01:01:59,200
Are you going to leave
without even telling me

641
01:02:00,400 --> 01:02:02,120
that you're actually Peeraka?

642
01:02:59,480 --> 01:03:01,840
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
